22/10/2002
ZAGREB, Croatia -- President Stipe Mesic met Monday (21 October) with Antoin Mac Unfraidh, chief of the EU monitoring mission, to discuss reforms related to Croatia's integration in the EU. They focused on the return of refugees and displaced persons, and relations with Yugoslavia and Bosnia and Herzegovina. As for relations with the UN war crimes tribunal, Mesic said that Croatia will observe its international obligations. Meanwhile, EU foreign ministers meeting in Luxembourg reiterated their stance, urging Croatia to co-operate with The Hague tribunal. (HINA, HRT - 21/10/02)
